==English==
===Etymology===
From the earlier [[punishment]] of [[behead|beheading]] [[criminal|criminals]]. The usage of this [[idiom]] began in the mid-1700s.
===Noun===
# A [[compensation]] for [[capture|capturing]] or [[kill|killing]] a person, ''esp.'' someone [[guilty]] of a [[crime]].
#: ''The [[police]] put a price on his head after he killed four innocent women.''
